"# Controlling the Problem\nControl measures, to be effective, must obey the same rules as human-waste disposal -simplicity and respect for the cultural context are essential. Four stages must be considered:\n. garbage collection at the household level -this involves providing households with trash cans or containers and organizing a garbage collection service. . transport to a dumping area -the dump must be away from the population and subject to strict hygiene measures to prevent the proliferation of communicable-disease vectors such as rats and flies. ."